column5: Activity Description
I’ve run twice this distance before with more energy to spare. Taking a week off really impacts my stamina
Pace was not as high, I didn’t want to do a second circuit until I got my new shoes and insoles

column3: Sunday morning recovery run with new shoes
column11: I was quite huffy puffy on this run, I’m here to test if my knees hurt over a 6k run. I have to do this 5 times before going back to the doc

column5: Super proud to push my self each Saturday with the crew. Week 4 of doing a pre-run before doing an easy pace run with this happy bunch!
Still a struggle after all this running this year. I’m getting better for sure.

8min X 4 splits 
Did a 5min30/km
This pace would be greater for a 10k

Big struggle on split 3
The last two runs have been super heavy on me. Heaviness like I lost months of training. I’ll be back Tuesday with plenty of sleep water and good food
Taking some time off from the stadium, the sunshine, the clocked sleep and food resulted in great energy on the track 🔥
I remember running on a the treadmill the first time and 10 minutes was impossible. I’ve come a long way to this steady run that lasted an hour
This is a great benchmark run- I didn’t run for 2 months and this is my first 2025 run it’s only going to get better 🔥
Super proud of doing 2X18 minute runs without stopping. I remember the struggle of doing even 2 laps around the track when I started!
It rained cats and dogs yesterday! Such a blessing for run day !
Pleasure run, stoped when I needed to, no rush to be anywhere. This number is only going to go UP!
Curious how Yoga helps me recover from runs

Super challenging to finish this run. I will need to take a nap after work - level tired. 
Glad I showed up. Saturday will be a pleasure run of not chasing any numbers.
The sun was out!

Ran back because why not 
Beast mode on 🔥

One of the first times on the track I did 5 rounds (330m each) and my heartbeat was at 201bpm. I’ve tried everything to bring this down 

Today was an endurance run and we did 15 rounds of the same track. My heartbeat beat at the end of it was 168bpm. 

I’ve conquered my heart ❤️
Love the PP crew, more friends joining the club ❤️

Did a super low effort run Tuesday and didn’t stop during any effort today 🔥 
2000m X 3 with 2-3m breaks in between. That’s 6 rounds round the track times 3 and I used to stop a handful of times each effort last year 
Not this time around 🔥

Made myself an exception and took the metro to the run 

Better than no run

Head above water but faaaar away from my sub 60 goal in June
Plateau phase is on

I wanted to do this run according to the target the coach set for the group - 3 X 10min runs with rest jogs in between. 
A. I didn’t rest jog, I stopped 
B. 3rd leg was too tight to carry on, so I stopped towards the end 

Feels like a failure at first- what can I do to reach this goal? Sleep? Check. Hydrate? Check. Recovery stretches? Double check.

At the end I realised that this goal was completely arbitrary and probably averages the athletes in our club. They’re goooood! 
If I compared myself to my previous runs, this is progress, but we’re all so hooked on arbitrary goals. 

Man running can teach us so much about life ! 

I didn’t study philosophy as a student, so I’m all geared up for this !

Can’t recognise myself running 17km on a rainy Saturday morning ! 
My identity has shifted to a fit person

Showing up in cold windy rain = Victory 🔥 
I’m a new person with this habit ❤️

Running without the coach being there is quite the thing ! 
I used to go for badminton classes as a child and would be overjoyed to just chill when the coach was absent 
Never understood the other kids who trained even during the coach’s absence 
I’m that kid now! A couple years older, but that kid nevertheless!

Finally back to interval training with the coach today. There were 10x of 30s on and 30s off, a 4 min break and 8x of 45s and 45s off. 
A friend of mine encouraged me to run with her and the first 10, I nailed. She’s way ahead of me on her running fitness and I was proud 🔥. Last 10s of this block, I abandoned her 

For the next block- 8x, tried as I might, it was a spectacle to watch me try to catch up. 
15-20s in, I’d have to slow down to keep my heart beat in sanity. 

Doing this painful training is the biggest secret of my running success this last 10 months (that’s all I’ve trained!) 
There’s also sleep and water and food, but the big performance gain comes from this interval training.

Can’t run yet from my ankle sprain from a week ago 😭 
Minimal thingy but I’m not doing 30km/week with a sensitive ankle 
Home workout it is

La reprise a été dur! Je me suis légèrement tordu la cheville il y a 2 semaines et choisi de le reposer. 
On était censé faire 8X 1000m avec une pause trottinette de 2 min entre les 1000 et j’en ai fait 4 propre et 2 moche. 
Cet effort <<decevant>> a terminé avec 8km d’effort et j’en suis fier. 
Je viens de loooiiinnnn et je vais faire que progresser. 
Les battement à 204 là, on peut dire que le coeur y était ❤️🔥

column3: Sortie longue + café + dej indien avec des potes
column5:
Je constate que j’ai plus les même problèmes qu’avant- les jambes et le corps n’atteignent pas leur limite lors une sortie longue comme avant. 
Je suis quand même essoufflé et c’est le battement de cœur qui est élevé.. avant c’était ça plus les jambes, le dos les épaules qui étaient épuisé. Il y a du progrès!!

After 2 days of rest I can still feel the weekend run in my glutes and calves. Shorter next weekend. 
26m endurance run and then 10x split training for 120m each. This workout was intense in its own right

No stats today, great feels 
Sun is out, I have the time for a peaceful run, no rushing back 
And I bought smoked salmon for €π

Each time I forget how exhausting this is. We did ab workouts after the whole split thing 
5* 60/60, 5*30/30, 5*15/45 and then the abs thingy 
I’m cooked

column3: The harder run of the week
column5:
We did a 4 2 2 4 X2 with 2m break between each effort. The 2m efforts were faster and hence more tiring than the 4s 
I have a run buddy who is way ahead of me and it has been an objective to keep her pace during split trainings. 
I succeeded today during the efforts. She still jogs the 2m breaks and I’m au bout du rouleau so I walk. But I kept her pace during the runs and that was a first. 🔥 
I’m leaving my precious group behind. The effort is paying off

Watching runners on YouTube, 10km in an hour has been the yardstick
You’re a runner? You’re doing 10k in an hour. I tried eleven months to up my game and constantly came short. Today however -I did it. 10.02km in 60m12 seconds. And then some. Apart from the health benefits to training, this is great for my mental space. Highly recommend-5 stars.
Ran with Manu today - he’s fast!

“Hard” doesn’t capture the struggle 
Back to my level in 2 weeks I bet

2 weekends of not resting enough shows on the track 
The harsh sunshine doesn’t help either. 
I really prefer running in the cold to the heat

column3: Travel screws my progress each time

column5: I have 12 data before my big race and it’s not looking good
I’m super proud of this 🔥 it’s only going to get better let’s goooooo

Better than skipping, I did half the workout and ended up feeling underwhelmed 
Great feeling !
If I didn’t post a story on Instagram, did I even run?

Never pushed my self to this heart rate before. Came in for a war and poured in all I had🔥 
I’m coming for the <55m 10k status in a week 
let’s goooo

38 this noon so we ran at 27 this morning and it was certainly a challenge. 
Last training before my 10k race this Sunday 😎
15° rainy and windy this morning. The muck didn’t help but I’m over the moon🔥
Didn’t stretch after the big run on Sunday and had zero energy to go. Glad to have showed up

Went way too fast on the first 3 laps and no juice in the end 
Rookie mistake occurance 3,142

Last run with the club before summer break !
It’s been a spectacular journey for me, and all my progress came from showing up here twice each week

column3: Taking a break from training run
Slow jog in the land down under
column5: Winter is sunny and I can’t ask for much else in life. ❤️
Slow, short, but run

It’s hard to let go of the figures and just cruise. I have this 54’ milestone I want to maintain and each kilometre, you see if you’re close or far, then you want to rush to close it in. 80% of the run should be speaking pace- I’m not that chill. I’ll try to be chill tomorrow over a shorter run.

column3: How did I not plateau Run
column5:
Quite thought provoking runs in the land down under, if I let my free self roll out a chill run, I do a 71 min 10k. How on gods green earth did I do a 54 min 10k a few weeks ago in Paris !?
Split training with the club had given me most of those gains and on performance mode, I know I can double down and push better figures.

What else am I plateauing on in life ? Strength when I do put in, is a modest home workout and maybe the split training equivalent would push progress Really efficiently. 
Flexibility and other personal goals too, with a group of people who’s been doing it for 2 decades, you get way better just by association.  

Coming from someone who is much faster, but sees how slow a pleasure run can be 
PS: a few 100m on the beach made my shoes all wet for the rest of the run and I have zero regrets

Did this run holding a conversation for 80% of it like the sensei says. 
Shorter distance was helpful 
Loving this new kind of holiday !

Only objective this morning was to yoga, home workout and do a slow run. 
Oh - and try a new coffee place everyone’s raving about in 🇦🇺 
I could get used to this

column3: 🇦🇺 finally turned on the winter switch
column5: Can’t believe I kept a higher pace than this for 54 minutes a few weeks ago! Loving that my rest also includes runs 😎 who am I !?

Back in the capital and split training🔥
Imagine this with sexion d’assaut’s mon gars sur !
1000kcal is easier on the court
Can’t believe I was a 54’ 10k a few months ago. It goes up and down
